Two  lovers reportedly committed suicide on Saturday, according to the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI), by jumping from the third floor of an apartment in Mtwapa’s Luxury area. According to tenants at the Bisgal Apartment, where the incident happened, the couple jumped from the balcony of their apartment on the third-floor at around 3.a.m . “According to the apartment’s guard, he heard a loud bang in the backyard, followed by the deafening noise of a car alarm that immediately went off.” a police report by the DCI said. “The guard went round to check what was happening, only to be confronted by the sight of a man’s naked body, lying on the ground,” The guard told the police that soon after, a second thud followed, and turned out to be the body of a woman. Detectives alerted to the matter visited the crime scene where they identified the deceased woman as 23-year-old Lucy Nyokabi. The man was only identified as “rastaman”. It was further established that the woman, a tenant at the apartment, was cohabiting with the man until her demise. “After accessing the house whose door had been latched from inside, detectives established that the two had been fighting prior to committing suicide,” the police report issued on Saturday reads. “The bedroom’s floor was flooded with blood while a glass table in the living room had been shattered”. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam